<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jan 29 21:46:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
During the time of the conflict I worked at a place that made packing for 500lb bombs,and I never gave it a thought <br>
about what I was doing. Now I wonder just what deth and destruction I was a part of. I though viet nam was just a <br>
name of a place far away with names that i could not pronounce. I still thought that way until 1992 when my new<br>
bride and i took a visit to the wall. From a distance as you <br>
walk up to it seems to call out,&quot;come and for a time join us<br>
and feel the pain and suffering we bore for you&quot;.<br>
I didn't think a wall could make me weep as I did'until I found the name of my brother in law,I touched his name and I <br>
could see his face and feel his heart beat,I never knew just how much i missed him untill that day. If you have never been there,&quot;Go&quot; and feel the pride of a nation and ask for <br>
forgivness.<br><br>
 Every person in the U.S. should go.<br>
 I just wish I could put into words the way i feel at this time.I love them all.<br><br>
If any one knew &quot;Roger Pinkley Crow&quot; while you were there<br>
 I would like to hear from you.<br>
Tonight Roger, This Bud's For you.<br>

